notes: This data layer is based on the model results of the 1999 National-Scale Assessment (N-SA), a part of the National Air Toxics Assessment (NATA), conducted by EPA's Office of Air Quality Planning & Standards (OAQPS). The assessment used computer models to estimate ambient air toxics concentrations and population exposures nationwide. Computer models were used since direct measurements of ambient air toxics concentrations are limited and direct personal exposure measurements are even more limited.
